<headline>Rip Current Statement issued December 28 at 3:56PM AST until December 30 at 6:00PM AST by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...HIGH RIP CURRENT RISK NOW IN EFFECT THROUGH THURSDAY
AFTERNOON...
* WHAT...Dangerous rip currents expected due to breaking waves
of 6 to 9 feet.
* WHERE...North-facing beaches of Puerto Rico, Culebra and
northern St. Thomas.
* WHEN...Through Thursday afternoon.
* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water.</description>
<instruction>Swim near a lifeguard. If caught in a rip current, relax and
float. Don`t swim against the current. If able, swim in a
direction following the shoreline. If unable to escape, face the
shore and call or wave for help.</instruction>
